Keith Moore (moore@cs.utk.edu) wrote:
: In practice, the ability to monitor (in real time) who is talking to
: whom, would be even more valuable than wiretaps for tracking
: "criminal" activity.  With Clipper, this could be done entirely with
: automatic machinery for very low cost.  This capability would dovetail
: quite well with the FBI digital telephony proposal's requirement to
: provide call setup data.
BZZZZT.  Sorry, it is already here, you can put a pen register on anyones
phone with almost no suspicion at all.  The technology is already here to
do this with telephone calls.  No future modification would be needed.

The only impediment to this is that the government has to do it one at a
time, due to law.  There is no "hard wired" protection at the moment.

Roger, Mad Dog Libertarian, Bryner.
